        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): classify structured unsupported model errors",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Preserve structured provider error details for failover classification without changing stored/displayed `errorMessage`.\n- Classify OpenAI-compatible `Not supported model <model-id>` details as `model_not_found` instead of schema/tool-payload failures.\n- Add typed assistant error metadata and full-path regression coverage for thrown SDK-shaped errors, assistant `errorBody`, user-facing payloads, and OpenAI-compatible transport loopback.\n\nCloses #92118\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: OpenAI-compatible providers can return HTTP 400 bodies where `error.message` is `Param Incorrect` while `error.param` contains `Not supported model <model-id>`. OpenClaw now classifies that as `model_not_found` and avoids misleading schema/tool-payload copy.\n\nReal environment tested: AWS Crabbox Linux lease `cbx_f55aeccc0a97` (`c7a.8xlarge`), run `run_de58983b891d`, using the dirty branch sync with a loopback OpenAI-compatible HTTP server returning the exact reported payload.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Crabbox script started a local `/v1/chat/completions` loopback server returning `{\"error\":{\"code\":\"400\",\"message\":\"Param Incorrect\",\"param\":\"Not supported model some-model-id\"}}`, then called `createOpenAICompletionsTransportStreamFn()` and checked `resolveFailoverReasonFromError()`, `classifyAssistantFailoverReason()`, and `formatUserFacingAssistantErrorText()`.\n\nEvidence after fix: The Crabbox proof printed `OPENCLAW_92118_FIXED_PROOF` with `dependencyShapeClassification.reason: \"model_not_found\"`, `classifications.assistantFailoverReason: \"model_not_found\"`, and user-facing text `The selected model was not found by the provider. Check the model id or choose a different model.`\n\nObserved result after fix: The exact reported payload no longer falls through to schema/tool-payload copy.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live third-party Xiaomi/MiFY credentialed provider call was not run; the proof uses a local OpenAI-compatible loopback server with the exact reported response body and real OpenClaw OpenAI-compatible transport.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` (ran twice after formatting; final result: clean, no accepted/actionable findings)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/live-model-errors.test.ts src/agents/failover-error.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.isbillingerrormessage.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.formatassistanterrortext.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/payloads.errors.test.ts src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts` (2 shards, 616 tests passed)\n- `../crabbox/bin/crabbox run --provider aws ...` (`run_de58983b891d`, `cbx_f55aeccc0a97`) for the reported loopback repro/fix proof\n- `git diff --check`\n",
        "branch": "fix/92118-structured-model-error-classification",
